    • getJsonDateTimeOrThrow

      public static java.time.LocalDateTime getJsonDateTimeOrThrow​(com.google.gson.JsonObject jsonObject, java.lang.String property)
      From 'jsonObject', get the value of 'property' and check that it can be converted into a LocalDateTime using the format "ISO-DATE" + "T" + "ISO-TIME", e.g. 2022-12-31T15:59:59.123456789 where the final NNNNNNNNN is the number of nano-seconds.

      This is the format from the UTC standard; we didn't make it up.

      If it is missing or cannot be parsed as a date with this format, throw an exception. Otherwise, return as a LocalDateTime.
